.TH AGENT-HOOK-POST-BASH 1 "2026-06-30" "agentguard" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-hook-post-bash \- scan agent shell command output after execution
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agent-hook-post-bash
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B agent-hook-post-bash
reads an agent hook JSON payload from standard input, extracts command stdout
from known agent payload shapes, and warns when output appears to contain
high-confidence credentials such as private keys or common API token formats.
.PP
The hook centralizes output extraction so agent-specific payload field names do
not leak into local extension policy.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The post-command scan completed. Credential findings are reported as warnings
rather than blocks.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR agent-hook-pre-bash (1)
